description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Rotherham NHS Foundation Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Assistant Practitioner&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Therapies and Dietetics&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Community Occupational Therapy Service&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 4 &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;37.5 hours per week , fixed term for 30 months.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Due to the present postholder being accepted on a course to become a qualified Occupational Therapist (OT) an exciting opportunity has arisen for an Assistant Practitioner to join the Community Occupational Therapy Service. Staff in this service work in Adult Social Care but are employed by The Rotherham NHS Foundation Trust. This is a fixed term contract for the length of the OT course. The Community OT Service is a jointly commissioned service between health and social care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will ideally have a relevant NVQ 3 and have experience of working in health or social care settings. You will work in the community, working under the supervision of senior staff, but with responsibility for your own caseload. You will be visiting disabled people and assessing their need for any equipment or adaptations and identifying their need for other services to enable them to live more independently. You may also be required to assist with moving and handling of individuals. You must be a car driver and have the use of a car for work. Good IT skills and computer literacy are also essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be based with the team in the South of the borough and you will be supported to do any relevant training you require.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information, please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jill Wilkinson, Clinical Lead OT, Therapies and Dietetics on 07725 487892.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;or email: jill.wilkinson2@nhs.net or jill.wilkinson@rotherham.gov.uk&lt;/p&gt;
